CSV Explorer
A modern, interactive CSV file viewer with advanced filtering, sorting, and visualization capabilities.

📋 Overview
CSV Explorer is a single-page application that allows you to upload CSV files and explore their data with an intuitive interface. It offers multiple views, powerful filtering options, column management, and data visualization - all without sending your data to any server.

✨ Features
File Management
CSV Upload - Drag and drop or click to upload CSV files

Smart parsing - Handles quoted fields, line breaks, and BOM markers

File information - Displays file size, row count, and column count

Data Exploration
Multiple Views

List View - Clean row-by-row display with key fields

Card View - Visual cards with tags and expanded fields

Table View - Traditional spreadsheet-style table

Overview - Summary statistics and data breakdowns

Filtering & Sorting
Smart Filtering - Filter by any column with multi-select options

Global Search - Search across all columns with Ctrl+K shortcut

Column Sorting - Sort by any column in ascending or descending order

Active Filter Pills - Visual indicators showing active filters

One-click Clear - Clear all filters with a single button

Column Management
Visible Columns - Choose which columns to display

Column Search - Quickly find columns in the sidebar

Primary Column - Automatically detected and highlighted

Column Order - Drag and reorder columns (UI ready)

Data Intelligence
Auto Type Detection - Identifies Text, Number, URL, Date, and Other fields

Data Summary - Real-time statistics about your data

Visual Breakdowns - Bar charts for categorical data in Overview view

Color Coding - Visual indicators for different data types

User Experience
Dark/Light Theme - Toggle between themes with persistence

Pagination - Browse large datasets with page controls

Responsive Design - Works on desktop, tablet, and mobile

Keyboard Shortcuts - Ctrl+K for quick search

Persistent State - Theme preference saved in localStorage

🚀 Getting Started
Prerequisites
Any modern web browser (Chrome, Firefox, Safari, Edge)

Quick Start
Download the project files (index.html, style.css, script.js)

Open index.html in your browser

Click "Upload CSV" or use the "Choose CSV" button

Start exploring your data!

Try It Now
No installation needed - just open the HTML file in your browser. All processing happens client-side.

📖 Usage Guide
Basic Workflow
Upload your CSV file

Browse data in your preferred view

Search or filter to find specific entries

Sort columns to organize data

Customize which columns are visible

Switch views for different perspectives

Keyboard Shortcuts
Ctrl+K - Focus search input

Esc - Close open dropdowns

Tips
The app automatically detects primary columns (name, title, tool, etc.)

URL columns become clickable links

Numeric fields (difficulty, priority, rating) show as dot scales

Categorical columns appear in filter dropdowns

The Overview view shows data breakdowns for top columns

